===Etymology===
[[c.]]1350–1400 {{etyl|enm}} ''sisoures'', from {{etyl|fro}} ''cisoires'', from {{etyl|VL.}} ''*cīsōria'', plural of {{etyl|LL.}} {{term|cīsōrium||cutting tool}} (compare {{term|chisel}}); from {{etyl|la}} word root ''-cīsus'' (compare {{term|excise}}) or {{term|cæsus}}, past participle of {{term|cædere||to cut}}.
* Current spelling, from the 16th century, is by association with {{etyl|ML.}} ''scissor'' (“tailor”), from {{etyl|la}} carrying the meaning “carver, cutter”, from {{term|scindere||to split|lang=la}}.

